<description>The most famous Japanese player of recent times, Hide is one of the few to play outside his home nation.
He began his career at J-League side Bellmare Hiratsuka making his debut in 1995.
He played at the 1996 Olympic games and made his full debut in May 1997 against South Korea. While at Bellmare Hiratsuka, he won the Asian Player of the Year in 1998 and played in the 1998 World Cup Finals.
This persuaded Serie A team Perugia to sign him for the 1998-99 season and he was a sensation scoring 13 goals from midfield. AS Roma signed him in January 2000 but after a difficult spell, he left to join Parma for ï¿½18.5 million in the summer of 2001.
He became a key player for Japan where he made full use of his ability to keep the ball and set up chances for the team 
Hidetoshi scored the second goal as Japan beat Tunisia 2-0 in Osaka in their final 2002 Group H game to secure qualification to the last 16 of the World Cup finals for the first time.</description>

